    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к *иран. %ivi-gand-%i, сращение преверба %ivi-%i с основой
        %igand-%i ‘осквернять’ и пр. Та же основа сохранилась в сращении с другим превербом:
        %ifæl-ǧændun%i (← *%ipari-gand%i) ‘окрашивать’. — Лексикализованное прош. причастие имеем в
        %iqæstæ%i | %iiǧæstæ%i ‘осквернение’ и пр. Глагол %iga(n)d-%i: %igasta-%i является
        общеиранским, восходит к и.е. *%ig˳edh-%i (*%ig˳endh-%i). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>gand</w><gloss><q>вонь</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><w>ganda</w><gloss><q>зловонный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><w>gandīdan</w><gloss><q>вонять</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>gandag</w><gloss><q>скверный</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ttt"
            ><lang/><w>valagandan</w><gloss><q>запачкать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>γandəl</w><gloss><q>чувствовать
            отвращение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"
                    ><lang/><w>γond</w><gloss><q>дурной</q></gloss></mentioned> (?), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*γandak(γndʼk,
            γntʼk)</w><gloss><q>дурной</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>зло</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*γaδken
                (γδkʼyn)</w><gloss><q>гадкий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><w>γanč (← *ganti-)</w><gloss><q>смрад</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>ganti-</w><gloss><q>смрад</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>gasta-</w><gloss><q>дурной</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="peo"><w/><gloss><q>зло</q></gloss></mentioned>, (=ос. %iǧæstæ%i, прош.
        причастие от *%igand-%i), <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>gandha-</w><gloss><q>запах</q></gloss></mentioned>. Значение ‘дурной’
        развилось из значения ‘смрад’, ср. ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyd"/> | %ifud%i
        ‘дурной’, ‘зло’ из *%iputa-%i ‘гнилой’, ‘смрадный’. За пределами иранских языков всего ближе
        по значению стоит к осетинскому славянская группа: <mentioned xml:lang="cu"
                ><lang/><w>гадь</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>гад, гадить,
                гадкий, гадость</w></mentioned> и пр. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_falǧændun"
        />, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qæstæ"/> | %iiǧæstæ%i.%n<bibl/>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to *Iranian %ivi-gand-%i, the fusion of the preverb %ivi-%i with
        the stem %igand-%i ‘to desecrate’ etc. The same stem is retained in the fusion of another
        preverb: %ifæl-ǧændun%i (← *%ipari-gand%i) ‘to paint’. — The lexicalized past participle is
        present in %iqæstæ%i | %iiǧæstæ%i ‘desecration’ etc. The verb %iga(n)d-%i: %igasta-%i is
        Pan-Iranian, it traces back to Indo-European *%ig˳edh-%i (*%ig˳endh-%i). Cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>gand</w><gloss><q>stench</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w>ganda</w><gloss><q>stinking</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w>gandīdan</w><gloss><q>to stink</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>gandag</w><gloss><q>nasty</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ttt"><lang/><w>valagandan</w><gloss><q>to
            dirty</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>γandəl</w><gloss><q>to
                    revolt</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"
                    ><lang/><w>γond</w><gloss><q>bad</q></gloss></mentioned> (?), <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*γandak(γndʼk,
            γntʼk)</w><gloss><q>bad</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>evil</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                ><w>*γaδken (γδkʼyn)</w><gloss><q>nasty</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><w>γanč (← *ganti-)</w><gloss><q>stink</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>ganti-</w><gloss><q>stink</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="peo"
            ><lang/><w>gasta-</w><gloss><q>nasty</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="peo"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>evil</q></gloss></mentioned>, (= Ossetic %iǧæstæ%i, past
        participle from *%igand-%i), <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><lang/><w>gandha-</w><gloss><q>smell</q></gloss></mentioned>. The meaning
        ‘nasty’ developed from the meaning ‘stench’, cf. Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fyd"
        /> | %ifud%i ‘nasty’, ‘evil’ from *%iputa-%i ‘rotten’, ‘stinkinh’. Beyond the bound of
        Iranian languages the Slavic group is the closest semantically to Ossetic: <mentioned
            xml:lang="cu"><lang/><w>гадь</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                    ><lang/><w>гад</w><gloss><q>vermin</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ru"><w>гадить</w><gloss><q>to make dirty</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ru"><w>гадкий</w><gloss><q>nasty</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ru"><w>гадость</w><gloss><q>nasty thing</q></gloss></mentioned>, etc. Cf. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_falǧændun"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qæstæ"/> |
                %iiǧæstæ%i.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
            /><biblScope>63</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
